-- LinkedIn Members Amend Hacking Complaint to Add Five Plaintiffs
-- B y   L i n d a   S a n d l e r
-- 2013-10-03T11:56:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-10-03/linkedin-members-amend-hacking-complaint-to-add-five-plaintiffs.html
LinkedIn Corp. members who sued the
professional-network company for allegedly hacking into their e-mail contacts amended a would-be class action complaint to add
five plaintiffs to the initial four, according to a filing in
federal court in  San Jose , California, yesterday. Plaintiffs who
joined include a lawyer, a corporate executive and a pediatrics
professor.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Linda Sandler in New York at 
 lsandler@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Farr at 
 sfarr@bloomberg.net  